{"altmetric_id":16235987,"counts":{"readers":{"mendeley":34,"citeulike":0,"connotea":0},"total":{"posts_count":14},"twitter":{"unique_users_count":13,"unique_users":["AmerGastroAssn","Crohnonlus","ResearchSurgeon","Suzanne78608267","MiracaGI","URW7","DrProvitaliz","inesmodolell","berkeleydoc","renumathyd","ElyseIreland","li_pd","jphysiol_eic"],"posts_count":13},"facebook":{"unique_users_count":1,"unique_users":["83243506953"],"posts_count":1}},"selected_quotes":["#Gastro review discusses pathophysiology, diagnosis, treatment of chronic #diarrhea","Happy to have published a new review on chronic diarrhea in Gastroenterology with Joe Sellin and Michael Camilleri"],"citation":{"abstract":"Chronic watery diarrhea poses a diagnostic and therapeutic challenge and is often a disabling condition for patients. Although acute diarrhea is likely to be caused by infection, the causes of chronic diarrhea (more than 4 weeks in duration) are more elusive. We review on the pathophysiology, diagnosis, and treatment of chronic diarrhea. Drawing on recent insights into the molecular mechanisms of intestinal epithelial transport and barrier function, we discuss how diarrhea can result from a decrease in luminal solute absorption, an increase in secretion, or both, as well as derangements in barrier properties. We also describe the various extra-epithelial factors that activate diarrheal mechanisms. Finally, clinical evaluation and tests used in assessment of patients presenting with chronic diarrhea are reviewed, and an algorithm guiding therapeutic decisions and pharmacotherapy is presented.","altmetric_jid":"4f6fa6193cf058f6100074fe","authors":["Michael Camilleri","Joseph H. Sellin","Kim E. Barrett"],"doi":"10.1053\/j.gastro.2016.10.014","first_seen_on":"2017-02-08T20:51:19+00:00","funders":["niaid"],"issns":["00165085","1528-0012"],"issue":"3","journal":"Gastroenterology","last_mentioned_on":1487698302,"links":["https:\/\/secure.jbs.elsevierhealth.com\/action\/getSharedSiteSession?r